Type check passes, everything looks good. Here's what I found and fixed:

### Changes

**TSX (`CountdownTimer.tsx`)**
- Split `formatTime` into `getSegments` (returns array of digit groups) + `formatTime` (joins for aria-label)
- Rendered time as separate `<span className="eva-countdown__digits">` and `<span className="eva-countdown__colon">` elements so colons can be targeted independently with CSS
- Colons are `aria-hidden="true"` since the full time string is in `aria-label`

**CSS (`CountdownTimer.css`)**

| State | Before | After |
|-------|--------|-------|
| **Normal** | Gold color only | Gold color + subtle dual-layer `text-shadow` backlight glow |
| **Warning** | Red pulse (`#ff2200`) | Amber pulse using `--eva-stripe` (`#ffaa00`), amber `text-shadow` glow |
| **Critical** | `berserk-text` color cycle only | Red `text-shadow` glow, `countdown-jitter` shake (0.3px translate steps), `countdown-colon-blink` (0.6s step blink) |
| **Expired** | Static red background | `countdown-expire-flash` — 1.2s flash sequence (bright → dim → bright → settle) with `forwards` fill |

- Added 3 new keyframes: `countdown-jitter`, `countdown-colon-blink`, `countdown-expire-flash`
- Updated `prefers-reduced-motion` to cover all new animations including colon blink and expired flash, with a static fallback background for expired state
